source_string: Add-Ons are a content type available in the Minecraft Marketplace that lets you add custom blocks, items, mobs, recipes, and other game content to your world.
translation: Add-Ons are a content type available in the Minecraft Marketplace that lets you add custom blocks, items, mobs, recipes, and other game content to your world.

source_string: Add-Ons allow you to modify your existing worlds and Realms through the Edit World screen and the Create New World screen.
translation: Add-Ons allow you to modify your existing worlds and Realms through the Edit World screen and the Create New World screen.

source_string: Stacking, or adding multiple Add-Ons, can increase loading times, and could result in unexpected results.
translation: Stacking, or adding multiple Add-Ons, can increase loading times, and could result in unexpected results.

source_string: We recommend that you save a copy of your world or Realm before adding or removing Add-Ons.
translation: We recommend that you save a copy of your world or Realm before adding or removing Add-Ons.

source_string: For more information about how you can make the most out of Add-Ons, you can visit our FAQ page.
translation: For more information about how you can make the most out of Add-Ons, you can visit our FAQ page.

source_string: Adventure Mode is a gamemode for world builders. In Adventure Mode, players must use special tools to place or break blocks.
translation: Adventure Mode is a gamemode for world builders. In Adventure Mode, players must use special tools to place or break blocks.

source_string: To get these special tools, you must use §e/give§f with §ecanplace§f or §ecandestroy§f parameters while in creative mode.
translation: To get these special tools, you must use §e/give§f with §ecanplace§f or §ecandestroy§f parameters while in creative mode.

source_string: Experience Levels can be used to repair, enchant, or rename items with the Anvil.
translation: Experience Levels can be used to repair, enchant, or rename items with the Anvil.

source_string: All items can be renamed, although only items with durability can be repaired or enchanted with Books on the Anvil.
translation: All items can be renamed, although only items with durability can be repaired or enchanted with Books on the Anvil.

source_string: An item can be repaired by placing it in one of the input slots on the left, along with either some raw materials of the item, like Iron Ingots for an Iron Sword, or combined with another item of the same type.
translation: An item can be repaired by placing it in one of the input slots on the left, along with either some raw materials of the item, like Iron Ingots for an Iron Sword, or combined with another item of the same type.

source_string: Combining items is more efficient when done with an Anvil.
translation: Combining items is more efficient when done with an Anvil.

source_string: There is a chance that the Anvil will be damaged with each use and after enough usage it will be destroyed.
translation: There is a chance that the Anvil will be damaged with each use and after enough usage it will be destroyed.

source_string: By wearing Armor, you can protect yourself from incoming damage. Your Armor level is represented by :armor: on the HUD, the higher the level, the less damage you will take.
translation: By wearing Armor, you can protect yourself from incoming damage. Your Armor level is represented by :armor: on the HUD, the higher the level, the less damage you will take.

source_string: Armor can be crafted from Leather, Iron, Gold, or Diamond. Chainmail Armor can be obtained through villager trading and loot from zombies and skeletons.
translation: Armor can be crafted from Leather, Iron, Gold, or Diamond. Chainmail Armor can be obtained through villager trading and loot from zombies and skeletons.

source_string: Equip Armor by opening your inventory and moving pieces of Armor to the appropriate slot next to your player skin.
translation: Equip Armor by opening your inventory and moving pieces of Armor to the appropriate slot next to your player skin.

source_string: Iron, Chainmail, and Golden Armor can be smelted into Iron or Gold Nuggets in a Furnace.
translation: Iron, Chainmail, and Golden Armor can be smelted into Iron or Gold Nuggets in a Furnace.
context: How To Play help text. {MaxLength="500"}

source_string: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press and hold :_input_key.sneak: to block with the Shield.
translation: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press and hold :_input_key.sneak: to block with the Shield.

source_string: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or press :_gamepad_stick_right: to toggle block with the Shield.
translation: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or press :_gamepad_stick_right: to toggle block with the Shield.

source_string: The Shield blocks all kinds of incoming damage - even a Creeper explosion! It can be equipped in the offhand slot or the hotbar.
translation: The Shield blocks all kinds of incoming damage - even a Creeper explosion! It can be equipped in the offhand slot or the hotbar.

source_string: When using the "D-Pad & tap to interact" control scheme, tap :touch_sneak: to toggle blocking with the shield.
translation: When using the "D-Pad & tap to interact" control scheme, tap :touch_sneak: to toggle blocking with the shield.

source_string: When using a "Joystick" control scheme, tap :tip_virtual_button_sneak: to toggle blocking with the shield.
translation: When using a "Joystick" control scheme, tap :tip_virtual_button_sneak: to toggle blocking with the shield.

source_string: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or click :rift_X: to toggle block with the Shield.
translation: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or click :rift_X: to toggle block with the Shield.

source_string: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or click :windowsmr_right_stick: to toggle block with the Shield.
translation: The Shield will block incoming damage. The Shield can be equipped in the offhand slot as well as the hotbar. Press :_input_key.sneak: or click :windowsmr_right_stick: to toggle block with the Shield.

source_string: The Shield can even block a Creeper explosion!
translation: The Shield can even block a Creeper explosion!

source_string: You can also wear a Carved Pumpkin on your head. This won't give you any :armor: but will make it so Endermen won't get mad when you look at them.
translation: You can also wear a Carved Pumpkin on your head. This won't give you any :armor: but will make it so Endermen won't get mad when you look at them.

source_string: An Armor Stand holds your armor while you aren't using it.
translation: An Armor Stand holds your armor while you aren't using it.

source_string: Press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand while holding a piece of armor to place it on the Armor Stand.
translation: Press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand while holding a piece of armor to place it on the Armor Stand.

source_string: Tap an Armor Stand while holding a piece of armor to place it on the Armor Stand.
translation: Tap an Armor Stand while holding a piece of armor to place it on the Armor Stand.

source_string: Press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand with an open hand to remove something from the Armor Stand.
translation: Press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand with an open hand to remove something from the Armor Stand.

source_string: Tap an Armor Stand with an open hand to remove something from the Armor Stand.
translation: Tap an Armor Stand with an open hand to remove something from the Armor Stand.

source_string: An Armor Stand can change its pose, sneak and press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand to change the pose.
translation: An Armor Stand can change its pose, sneak and press :_input_key.use: on an Armor Stand to change the pose.

source_string: An Armor Stand can change its pose, sneak and tap an Armor Stand to change the pose.
translation: An Armor Stand can change its pose, sneak and tap an Armor Stand to change the pose.

source_string: Armor Stands will react to a Redstone signal, try giving it different signal strengths and see what happens.
translation: Armor Stands will react to a Redstone signal, try giving it different signal strengths and see what happens.

source_string: Banners are a cool way to decorate your house or castle with custom patterns and colors.
translation: Banners are a cool way to decorate your house or castle with custom patterns and colors.

source_string: After crafting a Banner, you can put it on a Crafting Table or Loom and add different dyes to create your own unique, cool design!
translation: After crafting a Banner, you can put it on a Crafting Table or Loom and add different dyes to create your own unique, cool design!

source_string: There are many different patterns that you can create with your dye such as:
translation: There are many different patterns that you can create with your dye such as:

source_string: - Making a triangle will give you a chevron pattern.
translation: - Making a triangle will give you a chevron pattern.

source_string: - Making a cross gives you a cross pattern.
translation: - Making a cross gives you a cross pattern.

source_string: - Use an Oxeye Daisy to craft a flower pattern.
translation: - Use an Oxeye Daisy to craft a flower pattern.
context: How To Play help text. {MaxLength="500"}

source_string: Experiment with different combinations to get even more patterns!
translation: Experiment with different combinations to get even more patterns!

source_string: A Banner can also have multiple layers, allowing you to have more than one pattern on your Banner. If you don't like the last pattern you put on a Banner, you can wash the last layer off in a Cauldron.
translation: A Banner can also have multiple layers, allowing you to have more than one pattern on your Banner. If you don't like the last pattern you put on a Banner, you can wash the last layer off in a Cauldron.

source_string: If you want to copy a Banner, put it on the Crafting Table with a blank Banner.
translation: If you want to copy a Banner, put it on the Crafting Table with a blank Banner.

source_string: Active Beacons project a bright beam of light into the sky.
translation: Active Beacons project a bright beam of light into the sky.

source_string: They are crafted with Glass, Obsidian, and Nether Stars (which is obtained by defeating the Wither).
translation: They are crafted with Glass, Obsidian, and Nether Stars (which is obtained by defeating the Wither).

source_string: Beacons need to be on top of a Pyramid of Iron, Gold, Emerald, Diamond, or Netherite blocks with an unobstructed view of the sky.
translation: Beacons need to be on top of a Pyramid of Iron, Gold, Emerald, Diamond, or Netherite blocks with an unobstructed view of the sky.

source_string: The material that the Beacon is placed on has no effect on the power of the Beacon.
translation: The material that the Beacon is placed on has no effect on the power of the Beacon.

source_string: In the Beacon menu you can select one primary power for your Beacon. The more tiers your pyramid has the more powers you can have.
translation: In the Beacon menu you can select one primary power for your Beacon. The more tiers your pyramid has the more powers you can have.

source_string: To set the powers of your Beacon you must use a Netherite Ingot, Emerald, Diamond, Gold Ingot, or Iron Ingot in the payment slot.
translation: To set the powers of your Beacon you must use a Netherite Ingot, Emerald, Diamond, Gold Ingot, or Iron Ingot in the payment slot.

source_string: Once set, the powers will emanate from the Beacon indefinitely. Powers are granted to all nearby players.
translation: Once set, the powers will emanate from the Beacon indefinitely. Powers are granted to all nearby players.

source_string: To change the color of the beam, place a stained glass block in its path.
translation: To change the color of the beam, place a stained glass block in its path.

source_string: Sleeping in a Bed passes the night and sets your spawn point.
translation: Sleeping in a Bed passes the night and sets your spawn point.

source_string: Press :_input_key.use: on a Bed to go to sleep. This can only be done at night.
translation: Press :_input_key.use: on a Bed to go to sleep. This can only be done at night.

source_string: Tap a Bed to go to sleep. This can only be done at night.
translation: Tap a Bed to go to sleep. This can only be done at night.

source_string: If you are playing Multiplayer, everyone in the world must be in a Bed at the same time to pass the night.
translation: If you are playing Multiplayer, everyone in the world must be in a Bed at the same time to pass the night.

source_string: If your Bed is broken you will return to where you first spawned into the world.
translation: If your Bed is broken you will return to where you first spawned into the world.

source_string: Be careful when using a Bed in the Nether, it's usually too hot to sleep.
translation: Be careful when using a Bed in the Nether, it's usually too hot to sleep.

source_string: A soft bed lets you sleep through the night. You'll need wool to craft one, as well as a safe spot to place it.
translation: A soft bed lets you sleep through the night. You'll need wool to craft one, as well as a safe spot to place it.

source_string: Sleeping in a bed will also set your §espawn point§f, meaning that if you die, you'll reappear right back home!
translation: Sleeping in a bed will also set your §espawn point§f, meaning that if you die, you'll reappear right back home!

source_string: You can only fall asleep when it's cozy, like when it's nighttime or during a thunderstorm.
translation: You can only fall asleep when it's cozy, like when it's nighttime or during a thunderstorm.

source_string: The world of Minecraft is made from millions of blocks. Each one is breakable, collectable, and placeable. There are almost no limits to what you can build!
translation: The world of Minecraft is made from millions of blocks. Each one is breakable, collectable, and placeable. There are almost no limits to what you can build!

source_string: Most blocks you will have to find in the world, but some can only be crafted such as combining other blocks on a crafting table like a Redstone Block or smelted in a furnace like Glass.
translation: Most blocks you will have to find in the world, but some can only be crafted such as combining other blocks on a crafting table like a Redstone Block or smelted in a furnace like Glass.

source_string: Most blocks are not affected by gravity and can float in mid air, but some like Sand and Gravel, will fall if there is no block underneath them.
translation: Most blocks are not affected by gravity and can float in mid air, but some like Sand and Gravel, will fall if there is no block underneath them.

source_string: Here are some examples of the more interesting blocks in Minecraft:
translation: Here are some examples of the more interesting blocks in Minecraft:

source_string: §eGlass§f - This is a transparent block that is made by smelting Sand in a Furnace.
translation: §eGlass§f - This is a transparent block that is made by smelting Sand in a Furnace.

source_string: §eConcrete§f - This is made by dropping a Concrete Powder block into water.
translation: §eConcrete§f - This is made by dropping a Concrete Powder block into water.

source_string: §eTerracotta§f - This is found naturally in Badlands biomes or can be crafted and dyed from Clay that is found underwater. Terracotta can be made into Glazed Terracotta by smelting it in a Furnace.
translation: §eTerracotta§f - This is found naturally in Badlands biomes or can be crafted and dyed from Clay that is found underwater. Terracotta can be made into Glazed Terracotta by smelting it in a Furnace.

source_string: §eMagma Block§f - This is found naturally in the Nether, it gives off a little light and will burn whoever steps on it.
translation: §eMagma Block§f - This is found naturally in the Nether, it gives off a little light and will burn whoever steps on it.

source_string: §eCoarse Dirt§f - This is almost like a normal Dirt block but Grass can't grow on it. It can be found in Windswept Savanna and Old Growth Taiga biomes.
translation: §eCoarse Dirt§f - This is almost like a normal Dirt block but Grass can't grow on it. It can be found in Windswept Savanna and Old Growth Taiga biomes.
context: How To Play help text. {MaxLength="500"}

source_string: The Book and Quill lets you record your adventures. Tell your story by entering text into the pages. You can even change the title and the author! Sign the Book and Quill to finalize your work. The Book and Quill will be editable until it is signed.
translation: The Book and Quill lets you record your adventures. Tell your story by entering text into the pages. You can even change the title and the author! Sign the Book and Quill to finalize your work. The Book and Quill will be editable until it is signed.

source_string: Brewing potions requires a Brewing Stand. Every potion starts off with a bottle of water, which is made by filling a Glass Bottle with water from a Cauldron or water source.
translation: Brewing potions requires a Brewing Stand. Every potion starts off with a bottle of water, which is made by filling a Glass Bottle with water from a Cauldron or water source.

source_string: A Brewing Stand has three slots for creating different potions. One ingredient can be used over all three bottles, so always brew three potions at the same time to best use your resources.
translation: A Brewing Stand has three slots for creating different potions. One ingredient can be used over all three bottles, so always brew three potions at the same time to best use your resources.

source_string: Putting Nether Wart in the top position of the Brewing Stand will give you an Awkward Potion. This doesn't have any effect by itself, but creates a base potion that can be used to create more advanced potions.
translation: Putting Nether Wart in the top position of the Brewing Stand will give you an Awkward Potion. This doesn't have any effect by itself, but creates a base potion that can be used to create more advanced potions.

source_string: There are many potion effects to discover, experiment with different ingredients and combinations to become a true alchemist.
translation: There are many potion effects to discover, experiment with different ingredients and combinations to become a true alchemist.

source_string: How to Play: Building a Shelter
translation: How to Play: Building a Shelter

source_string: When danger comes lurking, a sturdy §eshelter§f can protect you from the threats outside.
translation: When danger comes lurking, a sturdy §eshelter§f can protect you from the threats outside.

source_string: Building a shelter is critical to surviving your first night, and it doesn't have to be hard.
translation: Building a shelter is critical to surviving your first night, and it doesn't have to be hard.

source_string: You can build one with anything from dirt to stone, or even close up a cave for a makeshift lodging!
translation: You can build one with anything from dirt to stone, or even close up a cave for a makeshift lodging!

source_string: The Cauldron is a container that can hold buckets or bottles of liquid.
translation: The Cauldron is a container that can hold buckets or bottles of liquid.

source_string: Press :_input_key.use: on a Cauldron while holding a Bucket of Water or a Potion to fill the Cauldron with its contents.
translation: Press :_input_key.use: on a Cauldron while holding a Bucket of Water or a Potion to fill the Cauldron with its contents.

source_string: Tap a Cauldron while holding a Bucket of Water or a Potion to fill the Cauldron with its contents.
translation: Tap a Cauldron while holding a Bucket of Water or a Potion to fill the Cauldron with its contents.

source_string: A Potion will only partially fill a Cauldron so you will have to use multiple Potions to fill it up completely.
translation: A Potion will only partially fill a Cauldron so you will have to use multiple Potions to fill it up completely.

source_string: Press :_input_key.use: on a Cauldron with your Arrow in hand to create all kinds of different arrows!
translation: Press :_input_key.use: on a Cauldron with your Arrow in hand to create all kinds of different arrows!

source_string: Tap a Cauldron with your Arrow in hand to create all kinds of different arrows!
translation: Tap a Cauldron with your Arrow in hand to create all kinds of different arrows!

source_string: To dye Leather Armor or Leather Horse Armor, press :_input_key.use: on a Cauldron filled with water while holding the desired dye. This will change the color of the water inside of the Cauldron. Then dip your armor into the Cauldron by pressing :_input_key.use: with armor in your hand.
translation: To dye Leather Armor or Leather Horse Armor, press :_input_key.use: on a Cauldron filled with water while holding the desired dye. This will change the color of the water inside of the Cauldron. Then dip your armor into the Cauldron by pressing :_input_key.use: with armor in your hand.

source_string: To dye Leather Armor or Leather Horse Armor, tap a Cauldron filled with water while holding the desired dye. This will change the color of the water inside of the Cauldron. Then dip your armor into the Cauldron by tapping the Cauldron with the armor in your hand.
translation: To dye Leather Armor or Leather Horse Armor, tap a Cauldron filled with water while holding the desired dye. This will change the color of the water inside of the Cauldron. Then dip your armor into the Cauldron by tapping the Cauldron with the armor in your hand.

source_string: If you want to wash the dye off, dip the dyed item into a Cauldron of undyed Water.
translation: If you want to wash the dye off, dip the dyed item into a Cauldron of undyed Water.

source_string: Press :_input_key.chat: to open Chat. Type your message and press ENTER.
translation: Press :_input_key.chat: to open Chat. Type your message and press ENTER.

source_string: Press :_input_key.chat: to open Chat. Type your message and press the send button.
translation: Press :_input_key.chat: to open Chat. Type your message and press the send button.

source_string: Tap the chat button to open Chat. Type your message and tap the send button.
translation: Tap the chat button to open Chat. Type your message and tap the send button.

source_string: Once you have crafted a Chest, you can place it in the world and then open it with :_input_key.use: to store items from your inventory.
translation: Once you have crafted a Chest, you can place it in the world and then open it with :_input_key.use: to store items from your inventory.

source_string: Once you have crafted a Chest, you can place it in the world and then tap to open it and store items from your inventory.
translation: Once you have crafted a Chest, you can place it in the world and then tap to open it and store items from your inventory.

source_string: Items in the Chest will be stored there for you to put into your inventory later.
translation: Items in the Chest will be stored there for you to put into your inventory later.

source_string: Two Chests placed next to each other will be combined to form a Large Chest.
translation: Two Chests placed next to each other will be combined to form a Large Chest.

source_string: Command Blocks are a powerful tool for map creators. They store and execute commands upon receiving a Redstone signal.
translation: Command Blocks are a powerful tool for map creators. They store and execute commands upon receiving a Redstone signal.

source_string: To get a command block you must use /give.
translation: To get a command block you must use /give.

source_string: When a Command Block has either executed or failed to execute its stored command, it sends a Redstone signal from the side where the arrow is pointing.
translation: When a Command Block has either executed or failed to execute its stored command, it sends a Redstone signal from the side where the arrow is pointing.

source_string: You can set the name of the Command Block in the Hover Note field.
translation: You can set the name of the Command Block in the Hover Note field.

source_string: §eBlock Type§f - There are three types of Command Blocks, each with their own color and behavior:
translation: §eBlock Type§f - There are three types of Command Blocks, each with their own color and behavior:

source_string: §eImpulse§f - Only executes the stored command when the block receives a redstone signal.
translation: §eImpulse§f - Only executes the stored command when the block receives a redstone signal.

source_string: §eChain§f - Executes the stored command when the Command Block behind it has or has not executed its command.
translation: §eChain§f - Executes the stored command when the Command Block behind it has or has not executed its command.

source_string: §eRepeat§f - Once activated, this Command Block will continue executing its stored command as long as it exists.
translation: §eRepeat§f - Once activated, this Command Block will continue executing its stored command as long as it exists.

source_string: §eCondition§f - There are two conditions, each will affect the behavior of the Command Block:
translation: §eCondition§f - There are two conditions, each will affect the behavior of the Command Block:

source_string: §eUnconditional§f - Executes the stored command even if the Command Block behind it failed to execute its command.
translation: §eUnconditional§f - Executes the stored command even if the Command Block behind it failed to execute its command.

source_string: §eConditional§f - Only executes the stored command if the Command Block behind it succeeded in executing its command.
translation: §eConditional§f - Only executes the stored command if the Command Block behind it succeeded in executing its command.

source_string: §eRedstone§f - There are two redstone settings, each will affect the behavior of the Command Block:
translation: §eRedstone§f - There are two redstone settings, each will affect the behavior of the Command Block:

source_string: §eNeeds Redstone§f - Requires a redstone signal to activate.
translation: §eNeeds Redstone§f - Requires a redstone signal to activate.

source_string: §eAlways Active§f - Does not require a redstone signal to activate.
translation: §eAlways Active§f - Does not require a redstone signal to activate.

source_string: A Command Block will also show you its previous output. This will help you figure out if a Command Block failed to execute its command and why.
translation: A Command Block will also show you its previous output. This will help you figure out if a Command Block failed to execute its command and why.

source_string: Commands can be executed from Chat. Type / before you type the command.
translation: Commands can be executed from Chat. Type / before you type the command.

source_string: There are multitudes of commands that will allow you to do amazing things. There are many sources out there that will provide you with all of the info that you'll ever need.
translation: There are multitudes of commands that will allow you to do amazing things. There are many sources out there that will provide you with all of the info that you'll ever need.

source_string: An active Conduit gives you powers when you are underwater and when it rains.
translation: An active Conduit gives you powers when you are underwater and when it rains.

source_string: A Conduit is crafted with Nautilus Shells and a Heart of the Sea. The Conduit draws power from Prismarine and Sea Lanterns.
translation: A Conduit is crafted with Nautilus Shells and a Heart of the Sea. The Conduit draws power from Prismarine and Sea Lanterns.

source_string: Once activated, a Conduit will grant Conduit Power to anything nearby.
translation: Once activated, a Conduit will grant Conduit Power to anything nearby.

source_string: The more power it draws in, the further its abilities reach.
translation: The more power it draws in, the further its abilities reach.

source_string: How to Play: Crafting a Tool
translation: How to Play: Crafting a Tool

source_string: §eTools§f help you get things done faster. Some, like the §epickaxe§f:wood_pickaxe: , let you mine stone and various ores. Others, like the §esword§f:wood_sword: , help you keep enemies at bay.
translation: §eTools§f help you get things done faster. Some, like the §epickaxe§f:wood_pickaxe: , let you mine stone and various ores. Others, like the §esword§f:wood_sword: , help you keep enemies at bay.

source_string: To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and right-clicking it. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!
translation: To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and right-clicking it. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!

source_string: To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and pressing :_input_key.use:. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!
translation: To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and pressing :_input_key.use:. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!

source_string: To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and tapping it. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!
translation: To craft a tool, open up your §ecrafting table§f:crafting_table: by walking up to it and tapping it. You can craft a basic version of most tools using two sticks and a few planks - your §erecipe book§f will tell you how!

source_string: To place or use certain Minecraft Education blocks or items, a player must possess a special ability called 'World Builder'.
translation: To place or use certain Minecraft Education blocks or items, a player must possess a special ability called 'World Builder'.

source_string: With cheats activated, the host can enable or disable the World Builder ability for any players in the world.
translation: With cheats activated, the host can enable or disable the World Builder ability for any players in the world.

source_string: To grant World Builder ability to all players in the world, run the following command:
translation: To grant World Builder ability to all players in the world, run the following command:

source_string: To quickly toggle your own World Builder ability, run either of the following commands:
translation: To quickly toggle your own World Builder ability, run either of the following commands:

source_string: To query your World Builder ability, run the following command:
translation: To query your World Builder ability, run the following command:

source_string: Minecraft Education features several special blocks that make it easier for teachers to create and employ lessons. Only players with World Builder ability can place and destroy these blocks. Only players without World Builder ability are subject to the restrictions imposed by these blocks.
translation: Minecraft Education features several special blocks that make it easier for teachers to create and employ lessons. Only players with World Builder ability can place and destroy these blocks. Only players without World Builder ability are subject to the restrictions imposed by these blocks.

source_string: Allow and Deny blocks control where players can build in a world.
translation: Allow and Deny blocks control where players can build in a world.

source_string: Players can place or destroy blocks above Allow blocks. Players cannot place or destroy blocks above Deny blocks.
translation: Players can place or destroy blocks above Allow blocks. Players cannot place or destroy blocks above Deny blocks.

source_string: Allow and Deny blocks do not affect the area below them.
translation: Allow and Deny blocks do not affect the area below them.

source_string: An Allow block with a Deny block somewhere below it prevents players from building in the space between the two blocks. Above the Allow block, players can place and destroy blocks.
translation: An Allow block with a Deny block somewhere below it prevents players from building in the space between the two blocks. Above the Allow block, players can place and destroy blocks.

source_string: Border blocks provide a force field that extends infinitely upward and downward, regardless of the presence of other blocks. Players cannot move through, over, or under a Border block. Players cannot place or destroy blocks that are above or below a Border block.
translation: Border blocks provide a force field that extends infinitely upward and downward, regardless of the presence of other blocks. Players cannot move through, over, or under a Border block. Players cannot place or destroy blocks that are above or below a Border block.

source_string: Minecraft is a §emultiplayer§f game by default.
translation: Minecraft is a §emultiplayer§f game by default.

source_string: Every new world you create starts with multiplayer enabled. If you want to make it §eprivate§f, go to World Settings to turn off multiplayer.
translation: Every new world you create starts with multiplayer enabled. If you want to make it §eprivate§f, go to World Settings to turn off multiplayer.

source_string: To play with others, go to the §eFriends tab§f to see all available Realms, Friends, and LAN games. Just select any game to join it.
translation: To play with others, go to the §eFriends tab§f to see all available Realms, Friends, and LAN games. Just select any game to join it.

source_string: When you start or join an online game, your friends can see this in their Friends tab. If they join, it'll be visible to their friends as well.
translation: When you start or join an online game, your friends can see this in their Friends tab. If they join, it'll be visible to their friends as well.

source_string: You need to be signed in to a §eMicrosoft account§f with an active internet connection to play multiplayer.
translation: You need to be signed in to a §eMicrosoft account§f with an active internet connection to play multiplayer.

source_string: Realms - The best way to play together
translation: Realms - The best way to play together

source_string: It's easy to play with friends using §eRealms§f.
translation: It's easy to play with friends using §eRealms§f.

source_string: You and up to 10 friends get 24/7 access to a world that's always online. Explore, get creative, or try curated content from Marketplace.
translation: You and up to 10 friends get 24/7 access to a world that's always online. Explore, get creative, or try curated content from Marketplace.

source_string: All you need is a paid Realms subscription. Why not try a free 30-day trial?
translation: All you need is a paid Realms subscription. Why not try a free 30-day trial?

source_string: You decide what people can do in your world by changing §eplayer permissions§f.
translation: You decide what people can do in your world by changing §eplayer permissions§f.

source_string: Open the game menu to see a list of players currently in your world, then select the permissions icon to adjust that player's permissions.
translation: Open the game menu to see a list of players currently in your world, then select the permissions icon to adjust that player's permissions.

source_string: Chalkboards are used to display text in the world. Chalkboards display more text than Signs, can be edited after they have been placed, and come in three sizes: Slate, Poster, and Board. The lock toggle allows you to prevent non-World Builders from destroying or editing your chalkboards. Press :_input_key.use: on an existing chalkboard to edit it.
translation: Chalkboards are used to display text in the world. Chalkboards display more text than Signs, can be edited after they have been placed, and come in three sizes: Slate, Poster, and Board. The lock toggle allows you to prevent non-World Builders from destroying or editing your chalkboards. Press :_input_key.use: on an existing chalkboard to edit it.

source_string: Chalkboards are used to display text in the world. Chalkboards display more text than Signs, can be edited after they have been placed, and come in three sizes: Slate, Poster, and Board. The lock toggle allows you to prevent non-World Builders from destroying or editing your chalkboards. Tap an existing chalkboard to edit it.
translation: Chalkboards are used to display text in the world. Chalkboards display more text than Signs, can be edited after they have been placed, and come in three sizes: Slate, Poster, and Board. The lock toggle allows you to prevent non-World Builders from destroying or editing your chalkboards. Tap an existing chalkboard to edit it.

source_string: Students can simulate real world chemistry by using the Chemistry Equipment blocks. Build any of the 118 different elements by adjusting the sliders in the Element Constructor or view the composition of elements by placing them in the Element Constructor. Combine elements in the Compound Creator to produce chemical compounds. Put elements and compounds into the Lab Table to create Minecraft items. Reduce blocks to their component elements with the Material Reducer.
translation: Students can simulate real world chemistry by using the Chemistry Equipment blocks. Build any of the 118 different elements by adjusting the sliders in the Element Constructor or view the composition of elements by placing them in the Element Constructor. Combine elements in the Compound Creator to produce chemical compounds. Put elements and compounds into the Lab Table to create Minecraft items. Reduce blocks to their component elements with the Material Reducer.

source_string: Download the Chemistry Journal from the Minecraft Education website for a comprehensive guide to chemistry in Minecraft.
translation: Download the Chemistry Journal from the Minecraft Education website for a comprehensive guide to chemistry in Minecraft.

source_string: NPCs are non-player characters that can provide additional lesson information, hints, or instructions.
translation: NPCs are non-player characters that can provide additional lesson information, hints, or instructions.

source_string: Only World Builders can place, delete, name, or edit NPCs. NPCs can execute commands and link to websites. Commands can be assigned to buttons in the NPC's dialog window; website links will always have a button.
translation: Only World Builders can place, delete, name, or edit NPCs. NPCs can execute commands and link to websites. Commands can be assigned to buttons in the NPC's dialog window; website links will always have a button.

source_string: NPCs have a variety of skins to choose from and are immobile.
translation: NPCs have a variety of skins to choose from and are immobile.

source_string: The Camera allows players to take pictures in the world.
translation: The Camera allows players to take pictures in the world.

source_string: To take a picture from your point of view, press :_input_key.use:.
translation: To take a picture from your point of view, press :_input_key.use:.

source_string: To take a picture from your point of view, tap and hold, then release.
translation: To take a picture from your point of view, tap and hold, then release.

source_string: To take a selfie, place a camera and press :_input_key.use: on it.
translation: To take a selfie, place a camera and press :_input_key.use: on it.

source_string: To take a selfie, place a camera and tap the Take Picture button.
translation: To take a selfie, place a camera and tap the Take Picture button.

source_string: Pictures can be viewed in the Portfolio or inserted into the Book and Quill.
translation: Pictures can be viewed in the Portfolio or inserted into the Book and Quill.

source_string: Pictures you have taken appear in the Portfolio. Press :_input_key.use: to view the Portfolio. When viewing the Portfolio, you can add captions to pictures, delete pictures, and export pictures as a PDF.
translation: Pictures you have taken appear in the Portfolio. Press :_input_key.use: to view the Portfolio. When viewing the Portfolio, you can add captions to pictures, delete pictures, and export pictures as a PDF.

source_string: Pictures you have taken appear in the Portfolio. Tap and hold to view the Portfolio. When viewing the Portfolio, you can add captions to pictures, delete pictures, and export pictures as a PDF.
translation: Pictures you have taken appear in the Portfolio. Tap and hold to view the Portfolio. When viewing the Portfolio, you can add captions to pictures, delete pictures, and export pictures as a PDF.

source_string: Classroom Mode is an external application that provides educators with features designed to facilitate interaction with students. You can download Classroom Mode from the Minecraft Education website.
translation: Classroom Mode is an external application that provides educators with features designed to facilitate interaction with students. You can download Classroom Mode from the Minecraft Education website.

source_string: As the host of a world, use the command /classroommode to launch the Classroom Mode app and connect it to Minecraft Education.
translation: As the host of a world, use the command /classroommode to launch the Classroom Mode app and connect it to Minecraft Education.

source_string: Code Builder allows players to explore, create, and play in Minecraft by writing code using familiar learn-to-code platforms.
translation: Code Builder allows players to explore, create, and play in Minecraft by writing code using familiar learn-to-code platforms.

source_string: Launch Code Builder by pressing :_input_key.codeBuilder: or by using the command /code.
translation: Launch Code Builder by pressing :_input_key.codeBuilder: or by using the command /code.

source_string: Launch Code Builder by tapping :code_builder_button: or by using the command /code.
translation: Launch Code Builder by tapping :code_builder_button: or by using the command /code.

source_string: The Crafting Table will let you craft more complicated recipes.
translation: The Crafting Table will let you craft more complicated recipes.

source_string: Place it in the world, then press :_input_key.use: on the Crafting Table to use it.
translation: Place it in the world, then press :_input_key.use: on the Crafting Table to use it.

source_string: Place it in the world, then tap the Crafting Table to use it.
translation: Place it in the world, then tap the Crafting Table to use it.

source_string: Creative Mode is there so you can build the land of your dreams mob free!
translation: Creative Mode is there so you can build the land of your dreams mob free!

source_string: The creative mode interface allows any item in the game to be moved into the player's inventory without the need for mining or crafting the item. The items in the player's inventory will not be removed when they are placed or used in the world, and this allows the player to focus on building rather than resource gathering.
translation: The creative mode interface allows any item in the game to be moved into the player's inventory without the need for mining or crafting the item. The items in the player's inventory will not be removed when they are placed or used in the world, and this allows the player to focus on building rather than resource gathering.

source_string: If you create, load, or save a world in Creative Mode, that world will have achievements and leaderboard updates disabled, even if it is then loaded in Survival Mode.
translation: If you create, load, or save a world in Creative Mode, that world will have achievements and leaderboard updates disabled, even if it is then loaded in Survival Mode.

source_string: To fly when in Creative Mode, press :_input_key.jump: twice quickly. To exit flying, repeat the action. To fly faster, push :_input_key.forward: twice in rapid succession or press :_input_key.sprint: while flying. When in flying mode, you can hold down :_input_key.jump: to move up and :_input_key.sneak: to move down.
translation: To fly when in Creative Mode, press :_input_key.jump: twice quickly. To exit flying, repeat the action. To fly faster, push :_input_key.forward: twice in rapid succession or press :_input_key.sprint: while flying. When in flying mode, you can hold down :_input_key.jump: to move up and :_input_key.sneak: to move down.

source_string: To fly when in Creative Mode, press :_input_key.jump: twice quickly. To exit flying, repeat the action. To fly faster, push :_gamepad_stick_left: forward twice in rapid succession while flying. When in flying mode, you can hold down :_input_key.jump: to move up and :_input_key.sneak: to move down.
translation: To fly when in Creative Mode, press :_input_key.jump: twice quickly. To exit flying, repeat the action. To fly faster, push :_gamepad_stick_left: forward twice in rapid succession while flying. When in flying mode, you can hold down :_input_key.jump: to move up and :_input_key.sneak: to move down.

source_string: To fly tap :tip_virtual_button_jump: twice quickly, and to stop flying tap :tip_virtual_button_fly_down: twice quickly.
translation: To fly tap :tip_virtual_button_jump: twice quickly, and to stop flying tap :tip_virtual_button_fly_down: twice quickly.

source_string: Tap :tip_virtual_button_sprint: to fly faster. To fly up tap and hold :tip_virtual_button_fly_up:, and to fly down tap and hold :tip_virtual_button_fly_down:.
translation: Tap :tip_virtual_button_sprint: to fly faster. To fly up tap and hold :tip_virtual_button_fly_up:, and to fly down tap and hold :tip_virtual_button_fly_down:.

source_string: To fly tap :touch_jump: twice quickly, and to stop flying tap :touch_stop_flying: twice quickly.
translation: To fly tap :touch_jump: twice quickly, and to stop flying tap :touch_stop_flying: twice quickly.

source_string: Tap :touch_forward: twice quickly to fly faster. To fly up tap and hold :touch_fly_up:, and to fly down tap and hold :touch_fly_down:.
translation: Tap :touch_forward: twice quickly to fly faster. To fly up tap and hold :touch_fly_up:, and to fly down tap and hold :touch_fly_down:.

source_string: How to Play: Death and Respawn
translation: How to Play: Death and Respawn

source_string: Enemies appear every night, and even the best of us can be caught off guard. If your §ehealth bar§f:heart: runs out, you'll die - and then respawn right where you started!
translation: Enemies appear every night, and even the best of us can be caught off guard. If your §ehealth bar§f:heart: runs out, you'll die - and then respawn right where you started!

source_string: You have unlimited lives, but you drop all items in your inventory when you die. If you're quick enough, you can pick your items back up right where you dropped them.
translation: You have unlimited lives, but you drop all items in your inventory when you die. If you're quick enough, you can pick your items back up right where you dropped them.

source_string: Minecraft has varying levels of difficulty so you can tailor the game to your level.
translation: Minecraft has varying levels of difficulty so you can tailor the game to your level.

source_string: No hostile mobs will spawn except for shulkers and the Ender Dragon, but they won't do any damage to you.
translation: No hostile mobs will spawn except for shulkers and the Ender Dragon, but they won't do any damage to you.

source_string: Hostile mobs spawn but deal less damage. Hunger bar depletes and drains health down to 5 hearts.
translation: Hostile mobs spawn but deal less damage. Hunger bar depletes and drains health down to 5 hearts.

source_string: Hostile mobs will do normal damage, and if your hunger level drops to zero your health will begin to drop, but you won't die.
translation: Hostile mobs will do normal damage, and if your hunger level drops to zero your health will begin to drop, but you won't die.

source_string: Hostile mobs will do more damage, zombies will break through doors, and if your hunger level drops to zero, your health will drop and you could die.
translation: Hostile mobs will do more damage, zombies will break through doors, and if your hunger level drops to zero, your health will drop and you could die.

source_string: Dispensers are used to shoot out items. You will need to power each Dispenser with a redstone signal (for example, with a lever) to trigger it.
translation: Dispensers are used to shoot out items. You will need to power each Dispenser with a redstone signal (for example, with a lever) to trigger it.

source_string: To fill a Dispenser with items, press :_input_key.use: on the Dispenser, then move the items that you want to dispense from your inventory to the Dispenser.
translation: To fill a Dispenser with items, press :_input_key.use: on the Dispenser, then move the items that you want to dispense from your inventory to the Dispenser.

source_string: To fill a Dispenser, tap the Dispenser, then move the items that you want to dispense from your inventory into the Dispenser.
translation: To fill a Dispenser, tap the Dispenser, then move the items that you want to dispense from your inventory into the Dispenser.

source_string: Whenever you power a Dispenser, an item will shoot out.
translation: Whenever you power a Dispenser, an item will shoot out.

source_string: Dispensers can also be used to place items as well, such as Pumpkins on Iron Golems and equipment on Armor Stands.
translation: Dispensers can also be used to place items as well, such as Pumpkins on Iron Golems and equipment on Armor Stands.

source_string: When powered by Redstone, Droppers will drop a single random item contained within. Press :_input_key.use: on the Dropper to open it and then you can load it with items from your inventory.
translation: When powered by Redstone, Droppers will drop a single random item contained within. Press :_input_key.use: on the Dropper to open it and then you can load it with items from your inventory.

source_string: When powered by Redstone, Droppers will drop a single random item contained within. Tap the Dropper to open it and then you can load it with items from your inventory.
translation: When powered by Redstone, Droppers will drop a single random item contained within. Tap the Dropper to open it and then you can load it with items from your inventory.

source_string: If a Dropper is facing a Chest or another type of container, the item will be placed into that instead. Long chains of Droppers can be constructed to transport items over a distance.
translation: If a Dropper is facing a Chest or another type of container, the item will be placed into that instead. Long chains of Droppers can be constructed to transport items over a distance.

source_string: Dye is used to change the color of many things in Minecraft.
translation: Dye is used to change the color of many things in Minecraft.

source_string: Some Dye materials are harder to find than others. Most Dyes can be crafted from flowers, like §eRed Dye§f from a Poppy, but some Dyes are found or created in more obscure ways such as:
translation: Some Dye materials are harder to find than others. Most Dyes can be crafted from flowers, like §eRed Dye§f from a Poppy, but some Dyes are found or created in more obscure ways such as:

source_string: §eBlue Dye§f - Mining Lapis Lazuli deep underground
translation: §eBlue Dye§f - Mining Lapis Lazuli deep underground

source_string: §eBlack Dye§f - Collecting Ink Sacs from Squids
translation: §eBlack Dye§f - Collecting Ink Sacs from Squids

source_string: §eBrown Dye§f - Harvesting Cocoa Beans in the Jungle
translation: §eBrown Dye§f - Harvesting Cocoa Beans in the Jungle

source_string: Elytra are an item that can be equipped to allow gliding. Elytra are equipped in the chest armor slot.
translation: Elytra are an item that can be equipped to allow gliding. Elytra are equipped in the chest armor slot.

source_string: Elytra cannot be crafted, but are found in Item Frames in rare End Ships, guarded by fearsome Shulkers.
translation: Elytra cannot be crafted, but are found in Item Frames in rare End Ships, guarded by fearsome Shulkers.

source_string: When equipped with Elytra, a player can press :_input_key.jump: while falling to start gliding. Note that you need to be quite high to really get the full effect!
translation: When equipped with Elytra, a player can press :_input_key.jump: while falling to start gliding. Note that you need to be quite high to really get the full effect!

source_string: When equipped with Elytra, tap :touch_jump: or :tip_virtual_button_fly_up: while falling to start gliding. Make sure you're high up to get the full effect!
translation: When equipped with Elytra, tap :touch_jump: or :tip_virtual_button_fly_up: while falling to start gliding. Make sure you're high up to get the full effect!

source_string: While gliding, you can steer by looking around. If you look downwards, you'll move faster - but you'll also hit the ground sooner. If you look upwards, you'll gain some height - but do it for too long and you'll stall, falling instead of rising!
translation: While gliding, you can steer by looking around. If you look downwards, you'll move faster - but you'll also hit the ground sooner. If you look upwards, you'll gain some height - but do it for too long and you'll stall, falling instead of rising!

source_string: You can steer while gliding by looking around. If you look downwards, you'll gain some speed, but you'll also hit the ground faster. If you look upward, you'll gain some height, but do it for too long and you'll stall - which means you'll start falling.
translation: You can steer while gliding by looking around. If you look downwards, you'll gain some speed, but you'll also hit the ground faster. If you look upward, you'll gain some height, but do it for too long and you'll stall - which means you'll start falling.

source_string: Your Elytra will slowly lose durability while flying, and if they break mid-flight you'll fall. You can repair them by combining them with Phantom Membrane at an Anvil.
translation: Your Elytra will slowly lose durability while flying, and if they break mid-flight you'll fall. You can repair them by combining them with Phantom Membrane at an Anvil.

source_string: Firework Rockets that have no effects can be used to extend Elytra flight. You will be damaged if you use a Firework Rocket that has effects to extend flight.
translation: Firework Rockets that have no effects can be used to extend Elytra flight. You will be damaged if you use a Firework Rocket that has effects to extend flight.

source_string: The Experience Points collected by picking up Experience Orbs can be used to enchant Weapons, Armor, Tools, and Books.
translation: The Experience Points collected by picking up Experience Orbs can be used to enchant Weapons, Armor, Tools, and Books.

source_string: When an enchantable item is placed in the slot below the book in the Enchanting Table, the three buttons to the right of the slot will display some enchantments with their Experience Level cost and Lapis Lazuli cost.
translation: When an enchantable item is placed in the slot below the book in the Enchanting Table, the three buttons to the right of the slot will display some enchantments with their Experience Level cost and Lapis Lazuli cost.
context: How To Play help text. {MaxLength="500"}

source_string: The actual enchantment applied is randomly selected based on the cost displayed.
translation: The actual enchantment applied is randomly selected based on the cost displayed.

source_string: If the Enchanting Table is surrounded by Bookshelves (up to a maximum of 15), with a one block gap between the Bookshelf and the Enchanting Table, arcane glyphs will be seen going to the book on the Enchanting Table and the potency of the enchantments will be increased.
translation: If the Enchanting Table is surrounded by Bookshelves (up to a maximum of 15), with a one block gap between the Bookshelf and the Enchanting Table, arcane glyphs will be seen going to the book on the Enchanting Table and the potency of the enchantments will be increased.
context: How To Play help text. {MaxLength="500"}

source_string: Enchanted Books are used at the Anvil to apply enchantments to items. This gives you more control over which enchantments you would like on your items.
translation: Enchanted Books are used at the Anvil to apply enchantments to items. This gives you more control over which enchantments you would like on your items.

source_string: After killing the Ender Dragon, an End Gateway will appear. Throwing an Ender Pearl into the portal will teleport you to the outer islands.
translation: After killing the Ender Dragon, an End Gateway will appear. Throwing an Ender Pearl into the portal will teleport you to the outer islands.

source_string: This alien new landscape must hide something interesting, and maybe something to bring back with you.
translation: This alien new landscape must hide something interesting, and maybe something to bring back with you.

source_string: All Ender Chests in a world are linked. Items placed into an Ender Chest are accessible in any other Ender Chest. However, the contents of the Ender Chests are specific for each player. This allows players to store items in any Ender Chest, and retrieve them from other Ender Chests in different positions in the world.
translation: All Ender Chests in a world are linked. Items placed into an Ender Chest are accessible in any other Ender Chest. However, the contents of the Ender Chests are specific for each player. This allows players to store items in any Ender Chest, and retrieve them from other Ender Chests in different positions in the world.

context: How To Play help text header. {MaxLength="80"}

source_string: Eyes of Ender are mysteriously connected to the End and will behave strangely when used.
translation: Eyes of Ender are mysteriously connected to the End and will behave strangely when used.

source_string: Rumor has it that they can lead you to open another dimension.
translation: Rumor has it that they can lead you to open another dimension.

source_string: There are a variety of different crops that you can farm in Minecraft. Farming, while challenging, can provide an infinite food source.
translation: There are a variety of different crops that you can farm in Minecraft. Farming, while challenging, can provide an infinite food source.

source_string: Crops require light, water, and farmland to grow. You need a hoe, a water source, and seeds to farm.
translation: Crops require light, water, and farmland to grow. You need a hoe, a water source, and seeds to farm.

source_string: The Blocks next to the water need to be converted to farmland, do this with the hoe. Water will saturate up to four block away.
translation: The Blocks next to the water need to be converted to farmland, do this with the hoe. Water will saturate up to four block away.

source_string: Now you can plant your seeds. Make sure your crops are protected as they can easily die from being trampled or lack of water or light.
translation: Now you can plant your seeds. Make sure your crops are protected as they can easily die from being trampled or lack of water or light.

source_string: Fences can help protect your crops from hungry rabbits or trampling toes!
translation: Fences can help protect your crops from hungry rabbits or trampling toes!

source_string: When the crops are fully grown they change in appearance and can be harvested.
translation: When the crops are fully grown they change in appearance and can be harvested.

source_string: Some plants like pumpkins and melons grow on stalks. Be careful not to harvest the stalks!
translation: Some plants like pumpkins and melons grow on stalks. Be careful not to harvest the stalks!

source_string: Fireworks are a fun way to create your own unique celebration in Minecraft!
translation: Fireworks are a fun way to create your own unique celebration in Minecraft!

source_string: Fireworks have two components, the Firework Rocket and the Firework Star.
translation: Fireworks have two components, the Firework Rocket and the Firework Star.

source_string: To use a Firework, press :_input_key.use: on a block to send the Firework shooting into the sky.
translation: To use a Firework, press :_input_key.use: on a block to send the Firework shooting into the sky.

source_string: To use a Firework, tap on a block to send the Firework shooting into the sky.
translation: To use a Firework, tap on a block to send the Firework shooting into the sky.

source_string: Fireworks have no effect other than shooting up into the air.
translation: Fireworks have no effect other than shooting up into the air.

source_string: Firework Stars can be added to during the crafting of the Firework Rocket to give it many different colors and effects.
translation: Firework Stars can be added to during the crafting of the Firework Rocket to give it many different colors and effects.

source_string: Firework Stars are made from gunpowder and various other items:
translation: Firework Stars are made from gunpowder and various other items:

source_string: §eColor§f - Adding dye of any color will make an explosion of that color.
translation: §eColor§f - Adding dye of any color will make an explosion of that color.

source_string: §eTwinkle§f - Adding Glowstone Dust will make the explosion twinkle.
translation: §eTwinkle§f - Adding Glowstone Dust will make the explosion twinkle.

source_string: §eCreeper Shaped§f - Adding a Head will make a creeper pattern in the sky.
translation: §eCreeper Shaped§f - Adding a Head will make a creeper pattern in the sky.

source_string: §eBurst§f - Adding a feather will give the explosion a burst effect.
translation: §eBurst§f - Adding a feather will give the explosion a burst effect.

source_string: §eTrail§f - Adding a Diamond will give the explosion trails.
translation: §eTrail§f - Adding a Diamond will give the explosion trails.

source_string: §eStar Shaped§f - Adding a Gold Nugget will make a star pattern in the sky.
translation: §eStar Shaped§f - Adding a Gold Nugget will make a star pattern in the sky.

source_string: Fireworks can be fired from a dispenser. This will shoot the Firework in the direction that the dispenser is facing.
translation: Fireworks can be fired from a dispenser. This will shoot the Firework in the direction that the dispenser is facing.

source_string: Fishing must be done with a Fishing Rod and is an excellent way to catch some fish or other cool items from the sea!
translation: Fishing must be done with a Fishing Rod and is an excellent way to catch some fish or other cool items from the sea!

source_string: Aim at a block of water and press :_input_key.use: while holding a fishing rod to cast the lure into the water.
translation: Aim at a block of water and press :_input_key.use: while holding a fishing rod to cast the lure into the water.

source_string: Look at a block of water and tap the Fish button while holding a Fishing Rod to cast the lure into the water.
translation: Look at a block of water and tap the Fish button while holding a Fishing Rod to cast the lure into the water.

source_string: Wait until you start to see a trail of bubbles coming for the lure.
translation: Wait until you start to see a trail of bubbles coming for the lure.

source_string: When the bubbles touch the lure, it will bob up and down. Press :_input_key.use: to reel in the lure. Be careful not to let your fish get away!
translation: When the bubbles touch the lure, it will bob up and down. Press :_input_key.use: to reel in the lure. Be careful not to let your fish get away!

source_string: When the bubbles touch the lure, it will bob up and down. Tap the Fish button again to reel in the lure. Be careful not to let your fish get away!
translation: When the bubbles touch the lure, it will bob up and down. Tap the Fish button again to reel in the lure. Be careful not to let your fish get away!

source_string: You'll slowly get hungry during your adventures - fortunately the Overworld is full of food! You can gather apples from trees, meat from animals, or why not grow your own crops using a hoe?
translation: You'll slowly get hungry during your adventures - fortunately the Overworld is full of food! You can gather apples from trees, meat from animals, or why not grow your own crops using a hoe?

source_string: To eat a food, select it in your hotbar, then click and hold the right mouse button. Keep the §ehunger bar§f:shank: full to regain health when you take damage.
translation: To eat a food, select it in your hotbar, then click and hold the right mouse button. Keep the §ehunger bar§f:shank: full to regain health when you take damage.

source_string: To eat a food, select it in your hotbar, then press and hold :_input_key.use:. Keep the §ehunger bar§f:shank: full to regain health when you take damage.
translation: To eat a food, select it in your hotbar, then press and hold :_input_key.use:. Keep the §ehunger bar§f:shank: full to regain health when you take damage.

source_string: To eat a food, select it in your hotbar, then tap the screen and hold. Keep the §ehunger bar§f:shank: full to regain health when you take damage.
translation: To eat a food, select it in your hotbar, then tap the screen and hold. Keep the §ehunger bar§f:shank: full to regain health when you take damage.

source_string: Some raw foods are better when cooked first on a campfire or in a furnace - your tummy will thank you!
translation: Some raw foods are better when cooked first on a campfire or in a furnace - your tummy will thank you!

source_string: A Furnace allows you to cook or smelt items. For example, you can smelt Iron Ore into Iron Ingots.
translation: A Furnace allows you to cook or smelt items. For example, you can smelt Iron Ore into Iron Ingots.

source_string: Place the Furnace in the world and press :_input_key.use: to use it.
translation: Place the Furnace in the world and press :_input_key.use: to use it.

source_string: Place the Furnace in the world and tap to use it.
translation: Place the Furnace in the world and tap to use it.

source_string: You need to put some fuel into the bottom of the Furnace, and the item that you want smelted in the top. The Furnace will then fire up and start working. Lots of things can be used as fuel; try experimenting with anything burnable!
translation: You need to put some fuel into the bottom of the Furnace, and the item that you want smelted in the top. The Furnace will then fire up and start working. Lots of things can be used as fuel; try experimenting with anything burnable!

source_string: When creating a world, you have many options. Below are the various settings that can be used to fine tune your experience. Don't worry if you didn't set them when you created the world, they can be changed at any time.
translation: When creating a world, you have many options. Below are the various settings that can be used to fine tune your experience. Don't worry if you didn't set them when you created the world, they can be changed at any time.

source_string: §eWorld Name§f: This is where you can name your world.
translation: §eWorld Name§f: This is where you can name your world.

source_string: §eDefault Game Mode§f: This is the gamemode that all new players to the world will start with. You can have players start in either survival or creative mode. Selecting creative mode will turn cheats on.
translation: §eDefault Game Mode§f: This is the gamemode that all new players to the world will start with. You can have players start in either survival or creative mode. Selecting creative mode will turn cheats on.

source_string: §eDifficulty§f: This setting affects how difficult the world will be. You can choose Peaceful, Easy, Normal, or Hard.
translation: §eDifficulty§f: This setting affects how difficult the world will be. You can choose Peaceful, Easy, Normal, or Hard.

source_string: §eStarting Map§f: If this setting is turned on, every player will start with a map in their hotbar.
translation: §eStarting Map§f: If this setting is turned on, every player will start with a map in their hotbar.

source_string: §eBonus Chest§f: If this setting is turned on, there will be a chest with some starting loot near your initial spawn location.
translation: §eBonus Chest§f: If this setting is turned on, there will be a chest with some starting loot near your initial spawn location.

source_string: §eWorld Type§f: This setting controls the way the world is created. Select Infinite or Flat from the drop down menu to change the world type.
translation: §eWorld Type§f: This setting controls the way the world is created. Select Infinite or Flat from the drop down menu to change the world type.

source_string: §eInfinite worlds§f go on and on forever.
translation: §eInfinite worlds§f go on and on forever.

source_string: §eFlat worlds§f do not have any hills or trees, just an infinite flat area to fill with your creations.
translation: §eFlat worlds§f do not have any hills or trees, just an infinite flat area to fill with your creations.

source_string: §eSeed§f: This is a unique number for the world. By entering a seed when you make a new world, you can control how it is created. You can also use a word or phrase for the seed and the game will convert it to a number for you.
translation: §eSeed§f: This is a unique number for the world. By entering a seed when you make a new world, you can control how it is created. You can also use a word or phrase for the seed and the game will convert it to a number for you.

source_string: §eActivate Cheats§f: This setting allows players to use commands. When a world is created with this setting on, all achievements are disabled.
translation: §eActivate Cheats§f: This setting allows players to use commands. When a world is created with this setting on, all achievements are disabled.

source_string: Below are gamerules, cheats must be turned on to use them:
translation: Below are gamerules, cheats must be turned on to use them:

source_string: §eAlways Day§f: Night will never fall when this setting is turned on.
translation: §eAlways Day§f: Night will never fall when this setting is turned on.

source_string: §eDaylight Cycle§f: The time will not advance when this setting is turned off.
translation: §eDaylight Cycle§f: The time will not advance when this setting is turned off.
context: How To Play help text. {MaxLength="500"}

source_string: §eKeep Inventory§f: This setting allows players to keep their inventory when they die.
translation: §eKeep Inventory§f: This setting allows players to keep their inventory when they die.

source_string: §eMob Spawning§f: This prevents all mobs from spawning when this setting is off.
translation: §eMob Spawning§f: This prevents all mobs from spawning when this setting is off.

source_string: §eMob Griefing§f: Prevents mobs from destroying the world.
translation: §eMob Griefing§f: Prevents mobs from destroying the world.

source_string: §eEntities Drop Loot§f: Controls whether things like minecarts and armor stands will drop themselves when they are broken.
translation: §eEntities Drop Loot§f: Controls whether things like minecarts and armor stands will drop themselves when they are broken.

source_string: §eWeather Cycle§f: The weather will not change when this setting is turned off.
translation: §eWeather Cycle§f: The weather will not change when this setting is turned off.

source_string: Hoppers are used to automatically move items. Hoppers can be attached to some other items like containers such as Chests or Jukeboxes.
translation: Hoppers are used to automatically move items. Hoppers can be attached to some other items like containers such as Chests or Jukeboxes.

source_string: Hoppers will continuously remove items out of a container placed above them and move them into the container they are pointing to.
translation: Hoppers will continuously remove items out of a container placed above them and move them into the container they are pointing to.

source_string: To make a Hopper point to a particular block, place the Hopper against that block while sneaking.
translation: To make a Hopper point to a particular block, place the Hopper against that block while sneaking.

source_string: If a Hopper is powered by Redstone, it will become inactive and stop moving items.
translation: If a Hopper is powered by Redstone, it will become inactive and stop moving items.

source_string: When playing with cheats on, host options will allow you to teleport yourself or friends, change the weather, set the time of day, and change the entry point or world spawn of your game. Once cheats have been enabled, you can find these options in the chat window by pressing the [/] button next to the chat bar.
translation: When playing with cheats on, host options will allow you to teleport yourself or friends, change the weather, set the time of day, and change the entry point or world spawn of your game. Once cheats have been enabled, you can find these options in the chat window by pressing the [/] button next to the chat bar.

source_string: When playing with cheats on, host options will allow you to teleport yourself or friends, change the weather, set the time of day, and change the entry point or world spawn of your game. Once cheats have been enabled, you can find these options in the chat window by tapping the chat button.
translation: When playing with cheats on, host options will allow you to teleport yourself or friends, change the weather, set the time of day, and change the entry point or world spawn of your game. Once cheats have been enabled, you can find these options in the chat window by tapping the chat button.

source_string: Use your tools a lot and they'll eventually break. As you gather new materials, such as stone, you'll be able to craft better tools.
translation: Use your tools a lot and they'll eventually break. As you gather new materials, such as stone, you'll be able to craft better tools.

source_string: Tools of higher tiers are more durable, more efficient, and able to gather more valuable resources. Go out into the world and find out for yourself!
translation: Tools of higher tiers are more durable, more efficient, and able to gather more valuable resources. Go out into the world and find out for yourself!

source_string: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Press :_input_key.inventory: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.
translation: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Press :_input_key.inventory: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.

source_string: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Tap :tip_touch_inventory: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.
translation: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Tap :tip_touch_inventory: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.

source_string: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Press :rift_B: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.
translation: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Press :rift_B: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.

source_string: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Press :windowsmr_left_grab: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.
translation: Your hotbar will fill up as you gather more resources. Press :windowsmr_left_grab: to access your §einventory§f, where you'll have more space for everything you've collected.

source_string: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Open your inventory, click the item of your choice, then drag it to the empty item slot you'd like to move it to.
translation: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Open your inventory, click the item of your choice, then drag it to the empty item slot you'd like to move it to.

source_string: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Use the cursor to select an item and press :_gamepad_face_button_down:. Then, move your cursor to an empty item slot and press again to drop the item.
translation: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Use the cursor to select an item and press :_gamepad_face_button_down:. Then, move your cursor to an empty item slot and press again to drop the item.

source_string: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Tap the item of your choice, then tap the empty item slot that you'd like to move it to.
translation: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Tap the item of your choice, then tap the empty item slot that you'd like to move it to.

source_string: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Use the cursor to select an item and press :_input_key.use:. Then, move your cursor to an empty item slot and press again to drop the item.
translation: Want to move something between your §ehotbar§f and your inventory? Use the cursor to select an item and press :_input_key.use:. Then, move your cursor to an empty item slot and press again to drop the item.

source_string: Jigsaw Blocks give creators the ability to generate large structures in the world by connecting multiple structure templates.
translation: Jigsaw Blocks give creators the ability to generate large structures in the world by connecting multiple structure templates.

source_string: To get a Jigsaw Block you must use the /give slash command. To use a Jigsaw Block, you must have Operator permissions.
translation: To get a Jigsaw Block you must use the /give slash command. To use a Jigsaw Block, you must have Operator permissions.

source_string: Jigsaw Blocks have multiple settings that control how they join together to form a larger structure.
translation: Jigsaw Blocks have multiple settings that control how they join together to form a larger structure.

source_string: §eTarget Pool§f - The path of the template pool to search for a connecting structure template. The template pool should contain at least one structure that matches the Jigsaw's "Target Name" field.
