translation: Using firework rockets boosts elytra speed in mid air. Just... make sure they don't explode, otherwise it'll hurt BADLY!

source_string: Riptide enchantment will propel you through the air in the rain.
translation: Riptide enchantment will propel you through the air in the rain.

source_string: The Beacon is a powerful item that can only be crafted with a Nether star from the Wither!
translation: The Beacon is a powerful item that can only be crafted with a Nether star from the Wither!

source_string: Nether stars can't be destroyed by explosions.
translation: Nether stars can't be destroyed by explosions.

source_string: Respawning in the Nether requires a charged respawn anchor.
translation: Respawning in the Nether requires a charged respawn anchor.

source_string: You can charge a respawn anchor with glowstone.
translation: You can charge a respawn anchor with glowstone.

source_string: You can breed hoglins with crimson fungus, but be careful.
translation: You can breed hoglins with crimson fungus, but be careful.

source_string: Gold is most common in the Nether and in the badlands biome.
translation: Gold is most common in the Nether and in the badlands biome.

source_string: Diorite, you either love it or hate it.
translation: Diorite, you either love it or hate it.

source_string: Take a screenshot using the Game menu.
translation: Take a screenshot using the Game menu.

source_string: A Realm is always online, so you and your friends can play here whenever you want.
translation: A Realm is always online, so you and your friends can play here whenever you want.

source_string: Keep up to date with what's going on in your Realm by checking the Story Feed in Realms Stories.
translation: Keep up to date with what's going on in your Realm by checking the Story Feed in Realms Stories.

source_string: Share your great moments with the other players on this Realm by adding a story to the Story Feed.
translation: Share your great moments with the other players on this Realm by adding a story to the Story Feed.

source_string: Check the Timeline in Realms Stories to find out when others are playing.
translation: Check the Timeline in Realms Stories to find out when others are playing.

source_string: Access Realms Stories from the game menu while playing on the Realm.
translation: Access Realms Stories from the game menu while playing on the Realm.

source_string: Get to know your Realm's community on the Members tab in Realms Stories.
translation: Get to know your Realm's community on the Members tab in Realms Stories.

source_string: Use Realms Stories to get social, keep up with your friends' progress, and organize playtime.
translation: Use Realms Stories to get social, keep up with your friends' progress, and organize playtime.

source_string: Bored of gravity? Jump twice to fly!
translation: Bored of gravity? Jump twice to fly!
context: A fun way to tell players that they can fly if they press the jump button twice.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Summon mobs in an instant with spawn eggs.
translation: Summon mobs in an instant with spawn eggs.
context: Players can use an item called Sawn Egg to summon animals and monsters.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Collect goat horns and fill the world with music.
translation: Collect goat horns and fill the world with music.
context: Goat horn is an object players can use to play loud sounds.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Combine flint and steel with a TNT block for explosive results.
translation: Combine flint and steel with a TNT block for explosive results.
context: Flint and steel is a tool used to create fire or to ignite certain blocks, structures and mobs. TNT will explode when you light it.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Try blinking around the map with an ender pearl. Don't get dizzy!
translation: Try blinking around the map with an ender pearl. Don't get dizzy!
context: An ender pearl is an item that can be thrown and teleports the thrower to where it lands.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Use rails and a minecart to build the perfect transport system. Or rollercoaster!
translation: Use rails and a minecart to build the perfect transport system. Or rollercoaster!
context: To  encourage players to build railroads{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Seeking a little more danger? Survival mode has plenty.
translation: Seeking a little more danger? Survival mode has plenty.
context: In the Game mode Survival mode you can die. In Creative you can’t.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Crossbows need ammo. Add some arrows to your inventory before going hunting.
translation: Crossbows need ammo. Add some arrows to your inventory before going hunting.
context: Crossbows need ammo. Add some arrows to your inventory before going hunting.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: You can't die, but villagers can. Use that information... wisely.
translation: You can't die, but villagers can. Use that information... wisely.
context: This means you can do things that will get villagers killed. Like attracting monsters to the village.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Villagers are great at building villages. Think you can do better?
translation: Villagers are great at building villages. Think you can do better?
context: This is a prompt to encourage players to build things.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Wolves will attack skeletons to chew on their tasty bones.
translation: Wolves will attack skeletons to chew on their tasty bones.
context: Wolves will attack skeletons. It’s also a discrete hint that you should feel wolves with bones to tame them.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Tame wild horses by sitting on them until they're calm, then saddle up and ride off. (Note: Horses do not work like that outside of Minecraft.)
translation: Tame wild horses by sitting on them until they're calm, then saddle up and ride off. (Note: Horses do not work like that outside of Minecraft.)
context: It’s a bit unintuitive how you tame horses. Most other animals are tamed by feeding them. Not Horses. {MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Eat as much as you want, you'll never get full! And you'll never starve.
translation: Eat as much as you want, you'll never get full! And you'll never starve.
context: In Creative Mode you don’t get hungry. Eating the food it just for fun.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Move through solid objects using spectator mode.
translation: Move through solid objects using spectator mode.
context: There is a Game mode called Spectator Mode. It allows you to fly through walls and blocks and everything.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Who needs tools? Punch your way to success and remove blocks instantly in creative mode.
translation: Who needs tools? Punch your way to success and remove blocks instantly in creative mode.
context: Block breaking happens very fast when you’re in Creative Mode.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Like what you see? Use the pick block button to start building with whatever you're looking at. Yes, even mobs!
translation: Like what you see? Use the pick block button to start building with whatever you're looking at. Yes, even mobs!
context: There is a feature called “Pick block” that enables players to instantly equip any block they click on. If you click on a mob(animal or monster) you will get a spawn egg that summons another monster/animal of that kind.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Get there now with the /tp command.
translation: Get there now with the /tp command.
context: You can teleport yourself in Creative. You use the /tp command in the chat.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Mobs won't notice you in creative mode, but they'll still notice each other…
translation: Mobs won't notice you in creative mode, but they'll still notice each other…
context: Mobs(animals & monsters) won’t notice you in creative mode, but they’ll still notice each other… meaning that they can still kill each other.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: A warden a day keeps the… well, everything away.
translation: A warden a day keeps the… well, everything away.
context: The Warden is a scary monster that live in underground cities.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Why not build an underwater base? It's not like you can drown.
translation: Why not build an underwater base? It's not like you can drown.
context: You can’t drown in creative mode. So it’s possible to build underwater without danger.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Whatever you can dream, you can build. There's no limit to your resources (in creative mode...).
translation: Whatever you can dream, you can build. There's no limit to your resources (in creative mode...).
context: Players have endless resources in Creative mode. They get all the building blocks from their inventory.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Phantoms can't hurt you, but you can still shoo them off by using a bed. Just...not literally. You sleep in it.
translation: Phantoms can't hurt you, but you can still shoo them off by using a bed. Just...not literally. You sleep in it.
context: Phantoms are flying mobs(monsters) that spawn when you havn't slept for a few days. They won't hurt you in Creative Mode. To get rid of them you sleep in a bed.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Have you tried swimming in lava? It's like sinking into a warm bath. Just don't try it in survival mode...
translation: Have you tried swimming in lava? It's like sinking into a warm bath. Just don't try it in survival mode...
context: Lava doesn't hurt you in creative mode.{MaxLength="200"}

source_string: Welcome to Minecraft Editor, a powerful tool for creating stunning Bedrock worlds with ease.[*newLine]Things work differently in Editor and it's important that you understand a few basics first or you might get lost.[*newLine]Let's dive into the basics.
translation: Welcome to Minecraft Editor, a powerful tool for creating stunning Bedrock worlds with ease.[*newLine]Things work differently in Editor and it's important that you understand a few basics first or you might get lost.[*newLine]Let's dive into the basics.

source_string: Set the font size for text in the Editor.
translation: Set the font size for text in the Editor.

source_string: Set the theme for the UI in Editor.
translation: Set the theme for the UI in Editor.

source_string: Set the size of the UI elements.
translation: Set the size of the UI elements.

source_string: We are so excited you're here and about to build with Minecraft's Bedrock Editor, where we want to empower Creators of all skillsets to easily create high-quality experiences.
translation: We are so excited you're here and about to build with Minecraft's Bedrock Editor, where we want to empower Creators of all skillsets to easily create high-quality experiences.

source_string: - There are two modes within the Editor: Tool or Crosshair. Tool is focused on using the multi-block editing tools as available via the UI and free-moving cursor, and Crosshair is for more precise, single-block edits using a crosshair in 1st person.
translation: - There are two modes within the Editor: Tool or Crosshair. Tool is focused on using the multi-block editing tools as available via the UI and free-moving cursor, and Crosshair is for more precise, single-block edits using a crosshair in 1st person.

source_string: - UI orientation: The left array of tools is referred to as the "toolrail", the top array is the "action bar" (eg. undo/redo), and the very top is the "menu" (eg. File).
translation: - UI orientation: The left array of tools is referred to as the "toolrail", the top array is the "action bar" (eg. undo/redo), and the very top is the "menu" (eg. File).

source_string: - For most UI actions and tools, there is a corresponding hotkey and sometimes a slash cmd.
translation: - For most UI actions and tools, there is a corresponding hotkey and sometimes a slash cmd.

source_string: - Rotate camera / unlock movement: In Tool, hold down right mouse button. In Crosshair, you do not need to hold down the right mouse button.
translation: - Rotate camera / unlock movement: In Tool, hold down right mouse button. In Crosshair, you do not need to hold down the right mouse button.

source_string: - Move on the XZ axis: WASD
translation: - Move on the XZ axis: WASD

source_string: - Move on the Y axis: E (up), Q (down)
translation: - Move on the Y axis: E (up), Q (down)

source_string: - Toggle between Tool and Crosshair Modes: (CTRL+TAB) or the UI button at the bottom of the viewport. When in Crosshair, you will need to use the hotkeys, though -- (CTRL+TAB) or ESC.
translation: - Toggle between Tool and Crosshair Modes: (CTRL+TAB) or the UI button at the bottom of the viewport. When in Crosshair, you will need to use the hotkeys, though -- (CTRL+TAB) or ESC.

translation: View the detailed directory of controls:

translation: Actions are shortcuts that live at the top of your screen. Hit the “+” button in the Action Bar to customize which are displayed.

source_string: At the top center of your screen is the Hotbar. Click once to change the active block, click twice to open the Block Picker to customize the Hotbar.
translation: At the top center of your screen is the Hotbar. Click once to change the active block, click twice to open the Block Picker to customize the Hotbar.

source_string: You can create a new Hotbar by clicking the Hotbar Menu button to the right.
translation: You can create a new Hotbar by clicking the Hotbar Menu button to the right.

translation: To navigate in the Editor, you’ll need a keyboard and mouse. Trackpads or controllers aren’t recommended.

source_string: Use WASD to move horizontally and Q & E to move vertically.

translation: Click on the Information button ("i") at the top right corner of each tool to learn more about how it works.
